Well, children
can be cruel.
Yeah.

490
00:24:01,241 --> 00:24:02,607
Great to see you, Bruce.
Nice to see you, sir.

491
00:24:02,609 --> 00:24:03,875
So, I had a question
for you, sir.

492
00:24:03,877 --> 00:24:05,377
Okay, hit me with it.

493
00:24:05,379 --> 00:24:06,912
Do you have any advice
on how to get adopted?

494
00:24:06,914 --> 00:24:08,046
Oh, yeah.
Oh, you do?

495
00:24:08,048 --> 00:24:09,080
Mr. Wayne,
can I get an autograph?

496
00:24:09,082 --> 00:24:10,882
Sure.

497
00:24:10,884 --> 00:24:12,250
Um, all right, for example,
is teeth whitener a good idea?

498
00:24:12,252 --> 00:24:13,552
Yes.
There you go, pal.
Thanks!

499
00:24:13,554 --> 00:24:14,820
Really?
Oh, yeah.

500
00:24:14,822 --> 00:24:16,421
Looking good, Bruce.
Thank you so much.

501
00:24:16,423 --> 00:24:18,423
How about eyeliner
or a foreign language?

502
00:24:18,425 --> 00:24:19,958
Try both.
<i> Bueno.</i>

503
00:24:19,960 --> 00:24:21,726
Look, it's
the new commissioner!

504
00:24:21,728 --> 00:24:23,462
Where?
Oh, she's with the mayor!
Okay. Let's see.

505
00:24:23,464 --> 00:24:24,596
Here she is, everyone!

506
00:24:24,598 --> 00:24:26,298
Oh, my darling!
Hi, dad.

507
00:24:26,300 --> 00:24:27,632
You look beautiful!

508
00:24:31,971 --> 00:24:33,738
Mr. Wayne?

509
00:24:33,740 --> 00:24:36,241
Should I get experimental
surgery to make my eyes larger

510
00:24:36,243 --> 00:24:37,709
and more vulnerable-looking?

511
00:24:39,078 --> 00:24:40,479
Uh, do that.

512
00:24:49,088 --> 00:24:50,856
Uh, Mr. Wayne?

513
00:24:50,858 --> 00:24:53,658
Are you currently
in the market
to adopt a child?

514
00:24:53,660 --> 00:24:55,260
Yeah.
Really?

515
00:24:55,262 --> 00:24:56,995
Oh, yeah.
Wow.

516
00:24:56,997 --> 00:24:58,830
Are you looking for more
of a base model orphan

517
00:24:58,832 --> 00:25:01,266
or one that has more
upgraded features?
Yep.

518
00:25:01,268 --> 00:25:02,801
Like cooking
or driftwood art?

519
00:25:02,803 --> 00:25:04,202
Gymnastic abilities?
Yep. Yep.

520
00:25:04,204 --> 00:25:05,837
Close-up street magic
a la David Blaine?

521
00:25:05,839 --> 00:25:07,839
All of it
sounds great.
Really?

522
00:25:07,841 --> 00:25:11,376
Because all of it
sounds like me.

523
00:25:11,378 --> 00:25:14,379
Mr. Wayne, do you think you'd
be interested in adopting me

524
00:25:14,381 --> 00:25:16,181
as your future orphan son?

525
00:25:16,183 --> 00:25:17,315
Definitely.

526
00:25:17,317 --> 00:25:18,884
Oh, this is great!

527
00:25:18,886 --> 00:25:20,552
Because all I want
is to get adopted,

528
00:25:20,554 --> 00:25:22,220
so I can finally stop being

529
00:25:24,690 --> 00:25:27,325
alone.

530
00:25:27,327 --> 00:25:28,727
<i> We've gathered </i>
<i> here tonight</i>

531
00:25:28,729 --> 00:25:30,862
<i> to mark the retirement</i>
<i> of Jim Gordon.</i>

532
00:25:30,864 --> 00:25:32,697
Goodbye.

533
00:25:32,699 --> 00:25:36,968
<i> And we wish him well on his</i>
<i> south African jungle safari!</i>

534
00:25:36,970 --> 00:25:38,136
Thank you.

535
00:25:38,138 --> 00:25:40,038
<i> Now, to introduce you</i>

536
00:25:40,040 --> 00:25:42,173
<i> to his exciting</i>
<i> new replacement.</i>

537
00:25:42,175 --> 00:25:44,843
<i> Everyone,</i>
<i> meet your new commissioner!</i>

538
00:25:46,713 --> 00:25:49,381
<i> Meet </i>
<i> Barbara Gordon!</i>

539
00:25:49,383 --> 00:25:52,717
<i> The new commissioner</i>
<i> of Gotham city!</i>

540
00:25:52,719 --> 00:25:54,185
Whoa!

541
00:25:54,187 --> 00:25:57,489
<i> She was top of her class</i>
<i> at Harvard for police.</i>

542
00:25:57,491 --> 00:25:58,990
<i> She cleaned up the streets</i>

543
00:25:58,992 --> 00:26:01,560
<i> of Gotham's nearby</i>
<i> sister city bludhaven</i>

544
00:26:01,562 --> 00:26:03,862
<i> using statistics</i>

545
00:26:03,864 --> 00:26:06,064
<i> and compassion.</i>

546
00:26:06,066 --> 00:26:08,833
<i> And now she's bringing</i>
<i> her new ideas</i>

547
00:26:08,835 --> 00:26:12,604
<i> and her nunchucks</i>
<i> to Gotham city.</i>

548
00:26:12,606 --> 00:26:14,739
Congratulations, darling.

549
00:26:14,741 --> 00:26:16,775
Thanks, dad.
Here she is, everyone!

550
00:26:16,777 --> 00:26:18,276
Thank you! Thanks!

551
00:26:18,278 --> 00:26:19,711
Hurray!

552
00:26:19,713 --> 00:26:20,912
Ms. Gordon,
over here!

553
00:26:20,914 --> 00:26:22,614
Big smile!
Wow.

554
00:26:22,616 --> 00:26:25,350
<i> Thank you for the oversized</i>
<i> key to arkham asylum.</i>

555
00:26:25,352 --> 00:26:27,252
<i> And, uh, what's this?</i>

556
00:26:27,254 --> 00:26:30,755
<i> Thank you for the switch</i>
<i> to the bat-signal.</i>

557
00:26:30,757 --> 00:26:32,090
<i> Nice.</i>

558
00:26:33,460 --> 00:26:36,595
<i> Dad, you've always</i>
<i> done a great job</i>

559
00:26:36,597 --> 00:26:38,530
<i> protecting Gotham city.</i>

560
00:26:38,532 --> 00:26:40,765
Flip!
That's me.

561
00:26:40,767 --> 00:26:43,735
<i> Thank you.</i>
<i> Along with Batman, of course.</i>

562
00:26:43,737 --> 00:26:45,270
Whoo!
Let's hear it for Batman!

563
00:26:45,272 --> 00:26:47,072
Who I wish
was here right now.

564
00:26:47,074 --> 00:26:48,773
Oh, I'm sure
he's listening.

565
00:26:48,775 --> 00:26:50,709
I'd like to ask
all of you a question.

566
00:26:50,711 --> 00:26:52,944
<i> Are you</i>
<i> fed up with crime?</i>

567
00:26:52,946 --> 00:26:54,045
Uh-huh.
We're all tired of crime.

568
00:26:54,047 --> 00:26:55,647
Yeah, we're sick of it.

569
00:26:55,649 --> 00:26:57,549
<i> Great. Then let's talk about</i>
<i> real improvements</i>

570
00:26:57,551 --> 00:26:59,784
<i> that will end</i>
<i> the cycle of crime.</i>

571
00:26:59,786 --> 00:27:01,753
<i> I've got a four-point</i>
<i> pilot program</i>

572
00:27:01,755 --> 00:27:03,288
<i> that I'd love</i>
<i> to share with you.</i>

573
00:27:03,290 --> 00:27:05,090
I wanna hear
all four points.

574
00:27:05,092 --> 00:27:06,291
It's called...
I am ready.

575
00:27:06,293 --> 00:27:07,425
It takes a village...

576
00:27:07,427 --> 00:27:09,060
Best opening
to a title ever.

577
00:27:09,062 --> 00:27:10,629
Not a Batman.

578
00:27:11,430 --> 00:27:12,464
Waiter.
Sir?

579
00:27:12,466 --> 00:27:13,598
Can I?
Of course.

580
00:27:13,600 --> 00:27:14,966
Thank you.
My pleasure.

581
00:27:14,968 --> 00:27:16,034
Thanks so much.

582
00:27:18,270 --> 00:27:20,105
What?
<i> Look.</i>

583
00:27:20,107 --> 00:27:24,109
<i> Batman's been on the job</i>
<i> for a very, very, very,</i>

584
00:27:24,111 --> 00:27:26,478
<i> very, very, very, very,</i>

585
00:27:26,480 --> 00:27:27,646
<i> very long time.</i>

586
00:27:27,648 --> 00:27:29,581
He has aged phenomenally.

587
00:27:29,583 --> 00:27:33,652
<i> However, despite all the great</i>
<i> work Batman has done for us,</i>

588
00:27:33,654 --> 00:27:35,620
<i> Gotham city</i>
<i> is still the most</i>

589
00:27:35,622 --> 00:27:38,590
<i> crime-ridden city</i>
<i> in the world.</i>

590
00:27:38,592 --> 00:27:39,991
She's got
a great point.
Interesting.

591
00:27:39,993 --> 00:27:41,926
Historically speaking,
that is accurate.

592
00:27:41,928 --> 00:27:43,495
<i> He hasn't captured riddler.</i>
You know,
she's right.

593
00:27:43,497 --> 00:27:44,996
<i> He hasn't captured bane.</i>

594
00:27:44,998 --> 00:27:47,098
Huh!
<i> Or catwoman.</i>

595
00:27:47,100 --> 00:27:51,136
<i> Or two-face, or any</i>
<i> of Gotham's other villains!</i>

596
00:27:51,138 --> 00:27:52,337
He's not good
at his job.

597
00:27:52,339 --> 00:27:54,005
<i> Including the joker!</i>

598
00:27:54,007 --> 00:27:56,107
She's making
a lot of sense.

599
00:27:56,109 --> 00:27:57,809
Excuse me.
I'm so sorry. Excuse me.

600
00:27:57,811 --> 00:27:59,511
We love you,
Barbara!

601
00:27:59,513 --> 00:28:01,446
Yes.
Hi. Bruce Wayne.

602
00:28:01,448 --> 00:28:03,515
Billionaire, bon vivant,
gallivanter, playboy,

603
00:28:03,517 --> 00:28:05,684
Gotham's most
eligible bachelor,

604
00:28:05,686 --> 00:28:06,818
like, 90 years in a row.

605
00:28:06,820 --> 00:28:08,119
That's me right there.

606
00:28:08,121 --> 00:28:09,187
<i> I know who you are,</i>
<i> Mr. Wayne.</i>

607
00:28:09,189 --> 00:28:10,789
You bet you do.
Quick quest,

608
00:28:10,791 --> 00:28:13,158
what is your problem
with Batman,

609
00:28:13,160 --> 00:28:15,660
and also,
what the heck, dude?

610
00:28:15,662 --> 00:28:17,295
<i> I'm glad you asked,</i>
<i> Mr. Wayne.</i>

611
00:28:17,297 --> 00:28:19,497
<i> I'm not a Batman hater.</i>

612
00:28:19,499 --> 00:28:22,067
<i> But we don't need</i>
<i> an unsupervised adult man</i>

613
00:28:22,069 --> 00:28:25,136
<i> karate-chopping poor people</i>
<i> in a Halloween costume.</i>

614
00:28:25,138 --> 00:28:27,872
<i> We need to take</i>
<i> what's good about Batman</i>

615
00:28:27,874 --> 00:28:32,644
<i> and marry it to actual laws</i>
<i> and proper ethics</i>

616
00:28:32,646 --> 00:28:34,212
<i> and accountability.</i>

617
00:28:34,214 --> 00:28:35,647
I hate everything
you just said.

618
00:28:35,649 --> 00:28:38,850
<i> Because my dream</i>
<i> is for the police force</i>

619
00:28:38,852 --> 00:28:40,719
<i> to team up with Batman.</i>

620
00:28:40,721 --> 00:28:42,087
Waiter.

621
00:28:42,089 --> 00:28:43,722
<i> Wouldn't that be better?</i>

622
00:28:43,724 --> 00:28:45,557
<i> And I know that, together,</i>

623
00:28:45,559 --> 00:28:47,559
<i> the world's</i>
<i> greatest detective...</i>

624
00:28:47,561 --> 00:28:49,728
<i> ...and Gotham's finest</i>

625
00:28:49,730 --> 00:28:52,030
<i> could clean up</i>
<i> these crime-ridden streets.</i>

626
00:28:54,034 --> 00:28:55,400
<i> Forever.</i>

627
00:28:55,402 --> 00:28:56,935
Everybody,
get down!

628
00:28:59,673 --> 00:29:01,740
Grand entrance!

629
00:29:01,742 --> 00:29:04,409
<i> Everyone! Make your way</i>
<i> to the exits immediately!</i>

630
00:29:04,411 --> 00:29:05,844
Run!

631
00:29:05,846 --> 00:29:07,879
Team bane,
block the exits.

632
00:29:07,881 --> 00:29:09,581
Going somewhere?

633
00:29:09,583 --> 00:29:12,250
Clayface, freeze, bring me
the new commissioner Gordon.

634
00:29:12,252 --> 00:29:14,052
We're on it.
Cool.

635
00:29:14,054 --> 00:29:16,020
And, Harley,
you know what to do.

636
00:29:16,022 --> 00:29:17,589
I sure do.

637
00:29:17,591 --> 00:29:20,925
It's time for operation
"take out the laundry."

638
00:29:20,927 --> 00:29:24,095
Butler one, this is
bat one. Do you copy?

639
00:29:24,097 --> 00:29:25,563
Go ahead, bat one.

640
00:29:25,565 --> 00:29:26,898
<i> I need my armored</i>
<i> face disguise, now!</i>

641
00:29:26,900 --> 00:29:28,399
Only if you say
the magic word.

642
00:29:28,401 --> 00:29:29,534
Now!
<i> No.</i>

643
00:29:29,536 --> 00:29:30,735
You're fired.

644
00:29:30,737 --> 00:29:32,604
No. Sir,
we'll talk about this

645
00:29:32,606 --> 00:29:33,671
back at the batcave.

646
00:29:35,908 --> 00:29:37,208
- Hey, 'puter.
<i>- Yes?</i>

647
00:29:37,210 --> 00:29:39,077
Initialize masterbuild music.

648
00:29:39,079 --> 00:29:40,912
<i> Right away.</i>

649
00:29:40,914 --> 00:29:44,115
<i> Collateral damage assessment</i>
<i> suggests the scuttler, sir.</i>

650
00:29:44,117 --> 00:29:45,283
Good plan.

651
00:29:50,089 --> 00:29:52,390
Madam mayor,
stay close to me.

652
00:29:52,392 --> 00:29:54,058
Head for the south exit.

653
00:29:54,060 --> 00:29:55,160
Now, ma'am.

654
00:29:57,063 --> 00:29:58,329
Go! Go! Go!

655
00:29:58,331 --> 00:29:59,764
Honey, let Batman
take care of it.

656
00:29:59,766 --> 00:30:01,299
Dad, I got this.

657
00:30:13,445 --> 00:30:15,113
<i> Scuttler online.</i>

658
00:30:15,115 --> 00:30:17,315
Chief O'Hara,
we're coming in hot!

659
00:30:17,317 --> 00:30:18,483
I'm almost there.

660
00:30:23,455 --> 00:30:26,157
Chief,
get the mayor to safety.

661
00:30:26,159 --> 00:30:28,660
Computer, I've got
the joker in my sights.

662
00:30:28,662 --> 00:30:30,829
Team, I got the joker
in my sights.

663
00:30:35,334 --> 00:30:36,467
Joker!

664
00:30:36,469 --> 00:30:37,702
Joker.

665
00:30:37,704 --> 00:30:39,304
Uh, excuse me?
I was about to...

666
00:30:39,306 --> 00:30:41,005
Push the bat-signal?
Good call.

667
00:30:41,007 --> 00:30:42,440
I like your instincts.

668
00:30:42,442 --> 00:30:44,342
I've got a surprise
for you guys.

669
00:30:44,344 --> 00:30:46,477
And it's gonna
make you smile.

670
00:30:46,479 --> 00:30:48,613
Uh-oh!
His smile is our grimace.

671
00:30:48,615 --> 00:30:49,681
Everybody, get down.

672
00:30:49,683 --> 00:30:50,815
I...

673
00:30:50,817 --> 00:30:51,883
Joker, no!

674
00:30:52,518 --> 00:30:53,985
...surrender.

675
00:30:53,987 --> 00:30:55,053
What?

676
00:30:56,488 --> 00:30:58,523
Uh, what did you just say?

677
00:30:58,525 --> 00:31:01,960
I said,
"i...Surrender."

678
00:31:01,962 --> 00:31:03,461
Joker,
what are you doing?

679
00:31:03,463 --> 00:31:05,363
I'm sorry, my bat-ears
must be malfunctioning

680
00:31:05,365 --> 00:31:06,497
because it sounds...

681
00:31:06,499 --> 00:31:08,066
I surrender!

682
00:31:08,068 --> 00:31:10,201
Okay, you know what? Cool it.
You're a criminal.

683
00:31:10,203 --> 00:31:12,370
You run,
and I catch you.

684
00:31:12,372 --> 00:31:13,872
Not anymore, Batman.

685
00:31:13,874 --> 00:31:16,040
You were right.
There is no "us."

686
00:31:16,042 --> 00:31:19,544
So, there's no point in me
trying to fight you anymore.

687
00:31:19,546 --> 00:31:22,046
Therefore,
i will be surrendering myself

688
00:31:22,048 --> 00:31:24,883
to our strong-willed
and forward-thinking
new commissioner.

689
00:31:24,885 --> 00:31:26,885
Blink, blink, blink.
Blinkety blink, blink, blink!

690
00:31:26,887 --> 00:31:28,253
That's really suspicious.

691
00:31:28,255 --> 00:31:30,221
Yeah, it is.
What are you up to, joker?

692
00:31:30,223 --> 00:31:32,857
I just wanna go to arkham
and pay for all of my crimes.

693
00:31:32,859 --> 00:31:34,659
Blink, blink, blink.
Blinkety blink, blink, blink!

694
00:31:34,661 --> 00:31:36,828
Are you actually
saying "blink"?

695
00:31:36,830 --> 00:31:38,229
No! Blink, blink, blink.

696
00:31:38,231 --> 00:31:39,397
<i> Joker! That's enough.</i>

697
00:31:39,399 --> 00:31:41,165
Okay, babs. I got this.

698
00:31:41,167 --> 00:31:44,736
Not so fast, Batman.
You can't fight me anymore.

699
00:31:44,738 --> 00:31:45,904
I'm off the market.

700
00:31:45,906 --> 00:31:47,839
What are you
talking about?

701
00:31:47,841 --> 00:31:49,741
I'm off the menu.

702
00:31:49,743 --> 00:31:52,877
You won't get to fight
any of this anymore.

703
00:31:52,879 --> 00:31:54,712
Man, am I sorry I asked.

704
00:31:54,714 --> 00:31:57,849
Anyway, have fun
in jail and...

705
00:31:57,851 --> 00:31:59,217
Batman, what are you doing?

706
00:31:59,219 --> 00:32:01,085
Punching bane.

707
00:32:01,087 --> 00:32:02,921
That was unnecessary.

708
00:32:02,923 --> 00:32:05,423
Oh, no, you can't fight bane
anymore either.

709
00:32:05,425 --> 00:32:06,925
Really?

710
00:32:06,927 --> 00:32:08,760
Yeah. Or riddler.

711
00:32:08,762 --> 00:32:10,328
Or catwoman.
Or condiment king.

712
00:32:11,063 --> 00:32:12,297
Why not?

713
00:32:12,299 --> 00:32:15,033
Because we're
all surrendering.

714
00:32:15,035 --> 00:32:16,200
Right, guys?

715
00:32:16,202 --> 00:32:17,268
We are?

716
00:32:17,270 --> 00:32:18,469
Yes!

717
00:32:26,212 --> 00:32:28,947
Riddle me this.
What just happened?

718
00:32:28,949 --> 00:32:30,615
It's the end of crime!

719
00:32:30,617 --> 00:32:32,050
All right!

720
00:32:32,052 --> 00:32:32,884
That was amazing!
Over here, over here!

721
00:32:32,886 --> 00:32:33,952
You did it!

722
00:32:33,954 --> 00:32:35,553
Yeah, of course
i did. I'm...

723
00:32:35,555 --> 00:32:36,754
Sorry, not you.

724
00:32:36,756 --> 00:32:38,489
We're talking
to commissioner Gordon.

725
00:32:38,491 --> 00:32:40,258
Well, it was
a team effort.
I got this, babs.

726
00:32:40,260 --> 00:32:41,793
Commissioner,
how do you feel?

727
00:32:41,795 --> 00:32:44,128
Amazing!
This is a great first day.

728
00:32:44,130 --> 00:32:45,463
Okay.

729
00:32:45,465 --> 00:32:47,098
Question for Batman.
Shoot.

730
00:32:47,100 --> 00:32:48,566
What are you gonna do
with the rest of your life?

